article.headline: Loyola, Md. 83, Marist 73
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Jamal Barney scored 22 points to lead five players in double figures aS Loyola-Maryland beat Marist 83-73 on Sunday. Marquis Sullivan made 5 of 10 3-pointers and had 17 points for the Greyhounds (8-12, 3-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who have won three consecutive games for the first time this season. Brett Harvey and Jawaan Wright each scored 13 points, and Brian Rudolph also added 11 for Loyola. Lawrence Williams and Ryan Schneider each had 15 points for the Red Foxes (7-13, 3-5), who have lost four of their past five games. R.J. Hall and David Devezin each had 11 points for Marist. With the game tied at 57, Harvey fueled a 13-3 run with eight points and the Greyhounds led 68-59 with 4:33 left. Barney added six consecutive points down the stretch, and Marist made just one field goal in the final 59.2 seconds.
